he original post that I am putting it here.<br>
<br>
Yes, the manual argument has been played out and heard by everyone and his brother.<br>
<br>
It's tired, it's old, and no one really cares. Especially not Mythic. That is why I don't post about it anymore. The one exception being when it was specifically ASKED for. You wanted my reasons and you got em.<br>
<br>
Whether or not it is valid is totaly trivial now. Mythic is not going to listen anymore now than they did in the beginning.<br>
<br>
I have moved on. Sure the old feeling are there, yet I ignore them for the useless dinosaurs they are. I now create my character over what I perceive to be effective and accomplishing my goal role.<br>
<br>
As of now I am playing more often. I am not a powergamer, my char is not the uber LEET of my server. I simply play now. I like luring mobs over to their faction enemies, then watching the proceeding gang rape =). It's cruel, I know, and it's only worth a tenth of the XP. However, it's hilarious to see and makes me grin evilly <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have abandoned all hope of ever being the rogue/mage hybrid I signed up for. It's just not gonna happen.<br>
<br>
Instead I play a more melee oriented rogue. Recently those debuff changes hit my char plans pretty hard. Envenom is no longer as strong as it was. So I've got some questions as to where I want my char to improve.<br>
<br>
All in all, I have decided to adapt to the changes. I cannot see myself playing as a pure caster. They get tons of spells, but I look upon the class as more of a target than an option. As for fighters, pure fighters take everything head on, right in the nose. I want to be the guy planting a curved dagger in their backs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Druids, bards, and all the rest? What, spend all my time healing and buffing John and Jane Doe? Heck no!<br>
<br>
My ideal is to play the Rogue. Go where others fear to tread, and strike when I decide to fight. This world isn't perfect, it is not what I read about or was told, yet I am determined to ring my satisfaction from this game on my terms. The other classes are different, less compelling. I will be a rogue because I am a rogue, heart and soul.<br>
<br>
Pedron Niall<br>
