<br>
Well see, there's your problem friend. In Dark Age of Camelot, classes aren't intended to be balanced against each other. The realms are intended to be balanced against each other through what each of all of their classes bring to the RvR table. <br>
<br>
The goal for each individual class is to have enough abilities to be able to solo blues effectively and offer something to a group. The variance amongst the classes is how much they offer to a group and how easily they solo yellows. <br>
<br>
You my friend have chosen to play the class that generally not only has trouble with yellows but isn't adored in groups either. In other words, you have chosen a challenging class to play. Are you up to the challenge? Or would you just rather whine that &quot;rogues suck?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzadokbaccarat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zadok Baccarat</A> at: 2/8/02 12:26:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubalorgafdan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balor Gafdan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 2:28:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2073.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Valarauco's Question</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Zadok.  Rogues are not meant to be as easily leveled as Heros.<br>
<br>
There not meant to be balanced against Blademasters, Heros, Paladins or any other class.  They are meant to be assassins in the field of realm versus realm.<br>
<br>
With such power comes a huge challenge.<br>
<br>
They limit our numbers by increasing our difficulty to effectively level.<br>
<br>
<br>
Bring on the challenge. <p><p><p style="text-align: left; font-size: 80%; font-family: Verdana">Balor Gafdan Nightshade of Guinivere<br><i>What life brings, is it ours to take?.<br>Adreneline feeds my soul, feeds my need<br>Kiss the blades edge I hold for thee.  Silence....</i></p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2073.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2073.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2073.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=2073.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=2073.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2073.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2073.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Mai